Confluence will perform automatic macro migration for every system restart. 
In some cases, an older version of macro can only runs on Wiki Markup. For this kind of situation, waiting for the macro to be upgraded in XHTML format can be time consuming and will force the System Administrator to disable this in the newer version of Confluence (with XHTML) to avoid error when opening a page containing this macro. (most of the time the macro won't work on the page) This is inconvenience for some users.

However, if Confluence has the ability to completely disable the automatic macro migration (and re-enable it at any time), the situation above can be solved.

