Same way we use templates and predefine certain labels into them it would be useful have the attachment macro be configurable to add specific label(s) if user drags a file into it to upload.

Example:
Let's say I am on a purchasing page of IT department and drag and drop for attachments is available on the page (via the attachment macro).  I want all attachments uploaded on this page to automatically have "purchasing" and "IT-department" labels (by default).  This way we can ensure that at minimum we have some high level labeling applied and we can ask the users to manually labels more specific labels such "invoice", "purchase order", etc. depending on the type of the purchasing document.
